The FCT Police Command has announced the arrest of a three-man gang behind the proliferation of fake COVID-19 exemption tags. This was contained in a statement on Monday by DSP Anjuguri Manzah, Police Public Relations Officer of the command. He disclosed that Police detectives from the Command Intelligence Bureau acting on tip-off, arrested the trio. “The suspects, Ahmed Adeiza ‘m’ 24 years, Oniya Arinze John ‘m’ 19 years and Donald Douglas ‘m’ 18 years, were arrested by police detectives on April 20, 2020 at UTC Garki Area 10 and Enugu Street Garki. “The exhibits recovered from Ahmed Adeiza include one fake FCT COVID-19 exemption tag, eight fake presidential Task Force exemption tags, two flash drives, one laptop, two fake Police Spy identity cards and some dried leaves suspected to be Indian hemp. “Oniya Arinza John and Donald Douglas were arrested in possession of ten fake FCT COVID-19 exemption tags. According to Ahmed Adeiza, each of the tags are sold at N1,500. “Since the commencement of this operation, the Command has arrested a total of nine suspects who produce the fake COVID-19 exemption tags, and seven suspects who obtained the fake tags and are using the same to defy the presidential lockdown order”, the spokesman added. The statement quoted the FCT Commissioner of Police, Bala Ciroma, as assuring that others still in the act would also be arrested and prosecuted